Pass --dangerously-bypass-approvals-and-sandbox to codex by default

The pod provides the sandbox, so codex does not need its own approval
gates or sandbox restrictions. This mirrors how claude gets
--dangerously-skip-permissions by default in rumpelpod.

Disable with --no-dangerously-bypass-approvals-and-sandbox on the CLI
or dangerously-bypass-approvals-and-sandbox = false in [codex] section
of .rumpelpod.toml.
